    <span id="ctl00_Content_lblNewsContent"><div>
<span style="font-size:18px">In preparation for the upcoming closure, the Bloom-Carroll Technology Department will be distributing Chromebooks to those parents with children who do not have at least one device at home that can be used for student use.</span><br>
</div>
<div>
<br><span style="font-size:18px">We are only able to issue one device per family member for those who do not have a working device at home. Pick up will be limited to only parents or guardians and you will need to sign a Chromebook loaner form at the time of pick-up. Parents are asked to call 740-756-9798 when they arrive at the traffic circle and a member of the technology department will deliver the device to your car. </span><br><br><span style="font-size:18px">If you have any questions regarding this procedure, please contact Mr. Mark Thomas at 740-756-9798 or by email at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="dcb1bdaeb7f2a8b4b3b1bdaf9cbeb0b3b3b1bfbdaeaeb3b0b0f2b3aebbf2">[email protected]</a></span>
</div></span>
